---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Paper Guides"
  description="Learn about the mission, community, and values behind Paper-Guides — a student-led open education project."
  canonical="https://paperguides.org/about"
>
  <!-- Dark top bar section -->
  <div class="mt-16 bg-[#242424] text-[#e2e0dc] py-16 px-5 md:px-30">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl font-serif font-bold mb-6">
        Welcome to <span style="color: var(--accent);">Paper-Guides</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Built by students, for students. Paper-Guides provides free exam
        preparation resources for CAIE A Levels, Kathmandu University, and
        beyond. We believe learning resources should never be gatekept or sold
        at inflated prices.
        <strong>Genuine access. No paywalls.</strong> No commission-based pricing.
        Just knowledge shared freely.
      </p>

      <!-- Social buttons -->
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3 text-[var(--color-text)]">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/chaulagainrupak/paper-guides"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-2 rounded-xl font-sans text-sm font-medium
                     shadow-md transition-all duration-300 ease-out hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:scale-[1.02]
                     bg-[var(--color-surface)] outline outline-1 outline-[var(--border-subtle)]"
        >
          <i class="ph-fill ph-github-logo text-[var(--pink-highlight)]"></i>
          GitHub
          <i
            class="ph-fill ph-arrow-square-out text-neutral-400 dark:text-neutral-500 text-xs"
          ></i>
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://discord.gg/U9fAnCgcu3"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-2 rounded-xl font-sans text-sm font-medium
                     shadow-md transition-all duration-300 ease-out hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:scale-[1.02]
                     bg-[var(--color-surface)] outline outline-1 outline-[var(--border-subtle)]"
        >
          <i class="ph-fill ph-discord-logo text-[var(--blue-highlight)]"></i>
          Discord
          <i
            class="ph-fill ph-arrow-square-out text-neutral-400 dark:text-neutral-500 text-xs"
          ></i>
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://instagram.com/paperguides.official"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-2 rounded-xl font-sans text-sm font-medium
                     shadow-md transition-all duration-300 ease-out hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:scale-[1.02]
                     bg-[var(--color-surface)] outline outline-1 outline-[var(--border-subtle)]"
        >
          <i class="ph-fill ph-instagram-logo text-[var(--accent)]"></i>
          Instagram
          <i
            class="ph-fill ph-arrow-square-out text-neutral-400 dark:text-neutral-500 text-xs"
          ></i>
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://www.youtube.com/@Paper-Guides"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-2 rounded-xl font-sans text-sm font-medium
                     shadow-md transition-all duration-300 ease-out hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:scale-[1.02]
                     bg-[var(--color-surface)] outline outline-1 outline-[var(--border-subtle)]"
        >
          <i class="ph-fill ph-youtube-logo text-[var(--pink-highlight)]"></i>
          YouTube
          <i
            class="ph-fill ph-arrow-square-out text-neutral-400 dark:text-neutral-500 text-xs"
          ></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Main content -->
  <div class="px-0 py-0">
    <div class="max-w-full">
      <!-- Grid: 2 columns, no gaps, sharp edges, full width -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 auto-rows-auto">
        <!-- Our Mission -->
        <div
          class="p-8 sm:p-12 shadow-lg border-r border-b border-slate-200/40 relative overflow-hidden bg-[var(--baby-powder)]"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 mb-4 relative z-10">
            <i class="ph-fill ph-target text-[var(--accent)] text-2xl shrink-0"
            ></i>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold">Our Mission</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed relative z-10">
            We're committed to providing quality resources without paywalls.
            Every student deserves access to past papers, study notes, and
            practice materials regardless of their financial background. Our
            platform eliminates the barriers schools and publishers create with
            expensive question banks and referral commissions. Knowledge is a
            right, not a commodity.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 100% Open Source -->
        <div
          class="p-8 sm:p-12 shadow-lg border-b border-slate-200/40 relative overflow-hidden bg-[var(--baby-powder)]"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 mb-4 relative z-10">
            <i
              class="ph-fill ph-code-simple text-[var(--jungle-green)] text-2xl shrink-0"
            ></i>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold">Open Source</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed relative z-10">
            Our codebase is fully open source on GitHub. The platform itself is
            transparent and auditable. However, our resource library (past
            papers, notes, and study materials) is curated and freely available
            to browse and download through the platform. If you need specific
            resources not yet available, email us and we'll work on adding them.
            This approach lets us maintain quality while keeping everything
            accessible.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Community-Driven -->
        <div
          class="p-8 sm:p-12 shadow-lg border-r border-b border-slate-200/40 relative overflow-hidden bg-[var(--baby-powder)]"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 mb-4 relative z-10">
            <i
              class="ph-fill ph-users-three text-[var(--french-blue)] text-2xl shrink-0"
            ></i>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold">Community</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed relative z-10">
            Paper-Guides exists because students decided to help other students.
            No corporate interests, no institutional backing with strings
            attached. Just peers sharing notes, papers, and insights. Our
            community grows because people genuinely care about making education
            accessible. Join Discord to connect with contributors, ask
            questions, and be part of something that actually benefits learners.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- How It Works -->
        <div
          class="p-8 sm:p-12 shadow-lg border-b border-slate-200/40 relative overflow-hidden bg-[var(--baby-powder)]"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 mb-4 relative z-10">
            <i
              class="ph-fill ph-lightbulb text-[var(--pink-highlight)] text-2xl shrink-0"
            ></i>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold">Get Started</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed relative z-10">
            Browse past papers organized by subject and year. Access study notes
            curated by students. Use our topic-wise question generator to create
            custom practice sets from specific chapters and topics. Search by
            subject code (like Physics 9702, Mathematics 9709, or Computer
            Science 9618 for A Levels) or by Kathmandu University programme.
            Everything is organized for maximum accessibility.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Full width: Get Involved + Contact -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 auto-rows-auto">
        <!-- Get Involved -->
        <div
          class="p-8 sm:p-12 shadow-lg bg-[var(--baby-powder)] border-r border-slate-200/40 relative overflow-hidden"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 mb-4 relative z-10">
            <i
              class="ph-fill ph-handshake text-[var(--blue-highlight)] text-2xl shrink-0"
            ></i>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold">Get Involved</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-5 relative z-10">
            You can make a real difference. Upload your study notes and exam
            papers to help other students. Suggest topics that need resources.
            Review and improve existing content. Write summaries or create new
            study guides. Every contribution gets you recognized in our
            community. Your work doesn't disappear into a corporate algorithm,
            it directly helps real students preparing for their exams.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 relative z-10">
            <a
              href="https://github.com/chaulagainrupak/paper-guides"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="group rounded-full px-4 py-2 flex items-center gap-2 bg-[var(--accent)] text-white shadow font-sans text-sm font-medium transition-all duration-300 ease-out hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:scale-[1.03]"
            >
              <i class="ph-fill ph-code"></i> View Code
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Contact -->
        <div
          class="p-8 sm:p-12 shadow-lg bg-[var(--baby-powder)] border-slate-200/40 relative overflow-hidden"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 mb-4 relative z-10">
            <i
              class="ph-fill ph-envelope text-[var(--green-highlight)] text-2xl shrink-0"
            ></i>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold">Contact</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="text-base mb-4 relative z-10">Questions or feedback?</p>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 relative z-10">
            <a
              href="mailto:contact@paperguides.org"
              class="text-base font-semibold text-[var(--accent)] hover:underline break-all"
            >
              contact@paperguides.org
            </a>
            <a
              href="mailto:paperguides.official@proton.me"
              class="text-base font-semibold text-[var(--accent)] hover:underline break-all"
            >
              paperguides.official@proton.me
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center py-6 px-8 border-t border-[var(--border-subtle)]">
        <p class="text-sm opacity-75">
          Thank you for supporting accessible education 🙌
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Featured Content Section for SEO -->
      <div class="px-8 sm:px-12 md:px-30 py-16 sr-only">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold mb-8">What We Offer</h2>

          <div
            class="space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-text)]"
          >
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-bold mb-2">
                CAIE A Level Past Papers
              </h3>
              <p>
                Access comprehensive past papers for Cambridge International
                Examinations A Levels. Our collection covers major subjects
                including Physics 9702, Mathematics 9709, Chemistry 9701,
                Biology 9700, Computer Science 9618, Economics 9708, Business
                9609, English Literature 9695, History 9389, and Geography 9696.
                Papers are organized by subject code and examination year,
                making it easy to find the exact papers you need for revision.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-bold mb-2">
                Kathmandu University Resources
              </h3>
              <p>
                Study materials for KU bachelor programs including BBA, BCA,
                BIM, BSc CSIT, BE Civil, BE Electrical, BE Computer, BE
                Electronics, BE Mechanical, BE Environmental Science, BSc
                Biotechnology, BSc Pharmacy and more. Papers are organized by
                faculty, programme, and semester for streamlined navigation and
                quick access to relevant materials.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-bold mb-2">
                Topic-Wise Question Generator
              </h3>
              <p>
                Create custom practice papers focused on specific topics and
                chapters. Unlike generic AI generators, our topic-wise system
                lets you target exact study areas. Want to practice only genetic
                inheritance questions? Or focus on thermodynamics for A Level
                Physics? Our generator curates questions specifically from your
                selected topics, giving you targeted, efficient practice
                sessions.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-bold mb-2">
                Study Notes Repository
              </h3>
              <p>
                Access detailed study notes compiled by experienced students.
                Notes cover concept explanations, worked examples, and exam
                tips. Every note is free, searchable, and organized by subject
                and topic. No paywalls. No premium tiers. All notes are openly
                shared so everyone benefits from the effort invested by
                contributors.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-bold mb-2">
                Why Paper-Guides is Different
              </h3>
              <p>
                Many institutions and publishers charge hefty fees for question
                banks and past papers, often incorporating hidden commission
                structures that inflate prices. Paper-Guides operates on the
                principle that educational resources should be freely available.
                We don't profit from student desperation during exam season. We
                don't partner with schools for referral commissions. We're built
                entirely by students who understand the financial pressures of
                education and believe learning materials must be accessible to
                everyone, regardless of economic background.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-bold mb-2">
                Request Missing Resources
              </h3>
              <p>
                Can't find past papers for a specific subject or programme?
                Email us at contact@paperguides.org and we'll prioritize adding
                them. Our community constantly works on expanding the
                collection, and user requests directly shape what gets added
                next. The more requests we get for a resource, the faster we
                work to include it.
              </p>
            </div>
            <p>
              By using Paper-Guides, you're supporting a model of education that
              prioritizes access over profit. When you contribute resources,
              you're directly helping hundreds of students prepare better for
              their exams. Our community proves that free, crowdsourced
              education can work at scale. Help us grow by sharing resources,
              inviting friends, and engaging with the community on Discord.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
